Endpoint Description
This endpoint retrieves student information from the server. It is designed to provide detailed personal, contact, academic, and extracurricular data for a specific student.
Request Format
•	Method: GET, PUT, POST, DELETE
•	URL: http://localhost:3000/Student
•	Request Body: The request expects a JSON payload containing the following structure:
JSON
{
  "personalInfo": {
    "firstName": "string",
    "lastName": "string",
    "dateOfBirth": "string (YYYY-MM-DD)",
    "gender": "string",
    "bloodGroup": "string"
  },
  "contact": {
    "email": "string",
    "phone": "string",
    "address": {
      "street": "string",
      "city": "string",
      "state": "string",
      "zipCode": "string",
      "country": "string"
    }
  },
  "academic": {
    "studentId": "string",
    "department": "string",
    "program": "string",
    "currentSemester": "integer",
    "enrollmentDate": "string (YYYY-MM-DD)",
    "expectedGraduation": "string (YYYY-MM-DD)",
    "gpa": "number",
    "status": "string"
  },
  "courses": [
    {
      "code": "string",
      "title": "string",
      "credits": "integer",
      "grade": "string",
      "semester": "string"
    }
  ],
  "extracurriculars": ["string"]
}
Response Structure
•	Status Code: 200
•	Content-Type: text/xml
•	Response Body: The response will be in XML format, although the specific content structure is not provided in the current documentation.
Notes
Ensure that the request body follows the specified format to avoid errors. The response will confirm the successful retrieval of the student information.

